<module status="bronze">
    <h>sguir</h>
    <p><g>sguir</g>
        <en>stop, cease, give up, leave off, desist</en> is a (regular) <a href="?xx=verbs/verbs"
            >verb</a>, marking <a href="?q=verbal_aspect">cessative</a> verbal aspect, cf. <a
            href="?gd=stad"><g>stad</g></a>
        <vb/>
        <en>stop, halt, pause</en>, <a href="?gd=crìoch"><g>crìoch</g></a>
        <fem/>
        <en>end, boundary</en>.</p>

    <section id="forms">
        <h>forms</h>
        <p>The principal parts of <g>sguir</g> are – <ul>
                <li><m>sguiridh</m> – future independent ie. <en>will stop</en></li>
                <li><m>sguir</m> – past independent ie. <en>stopped</en></li>
                <li><m>sgur</m> – verbal noun ie. <en>stopping</en></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
