    <section>
        <h>dependents</h>
        <section id="deps-sbj">
            <h>subject</h>
            <p>The subject of <g>sguir</g> is generally a noun expression denoting a human (or other animal) – <ul>
                    <li><m>Sguir mi.</m>
                        <en>I stopped.</en></li>
                    <li><m>Sguir!</m>
                        <en>Stop!</en></li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p>Some examples – <ul id="deps-sbj-hum-xs">
                    <li>pedagogical examples – <xl id="deps-sbj-hum-pedag">
                            <li>
                                <gd>Sguir sinn aig meadhan-làtha.</gd>
                                <tr>We stopped at noon.</tr>
                                <ref text="605">td. 334</ref>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <gd>Sguiribh anns a’ bhad!</gd>
                                <tr>Stop at once!</tr>
                                <ref text="601">td. 524</ref>
                            </li>
                        </xl>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p>The subject of <g>sguir</g> can also denoting an inanimate object – <ul>
                    <li><m>Sguir an togalach a luasgadh.</m>
                        <en>The building stopped shaking.</en></li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p>Some examples – <ul id="deps-sbj-inanim-xs">
                    <li>pedagogical examples – <xl id="deps-sbj-inanim-pedag">
                            <li>
                                <gd>Sguir na gunnachan a losgadh.</gd>
                                <tr>The guns stopped firing.</tr>
                                <ref text="601">td. 524</ref>
                            </li>
                        </xl>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p>Sometimes the subject of <g>sguir</g> can be more abstract – <ul>
                    <li><m>Sguir an sneachd.</m>
                        <en>The snow stopped.</en></li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p>Some examples – <ul id="deps-sbj-abs-xs">
                    <li>pedagogical examples – <xl id="deps-sbj-abs-pedag">
                            <li>
                                <gd>An do sguir an t-uisge?</gd>
                                <tr>Has the rain stopped?</tr>
                                <ref text="601">td. 524</ref>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <gd>Ann an tiota sguir e.</gd>
                                <tr>In an instant it stopped.</tr>
                                <ref text="601">td. 524</ref>
                            </li>
                        </xl></li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="deps-comps">
            <h>complements</h>
            <section id="deps-comp-none">
                <h>strict intransitive</h>
                <p><g>sguir</g> can occur without any complements, as a strict intransitive verb – <ul>
                        <li><m>Sguir sinn.</m>
                            <en>We stopped.</en></li>
                        <li><m>Sguir!</m>
                            <en>Stop!</en></li>
                        <li><m>Sguir an sneachd.</m>
                            <en>The snow stopped.</en></li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h>prepositions</h>
                <module id="deps-comps-dhe" status="bronze">
                    <h>sguir de [a] ...</h>
                    <p><g>sguir</g> can take a (verbal noun) complement introduced by the
                        preposition <a href="?gd=de"><g>de</g> [<g>a</g>]</a>
                        <en>of</en> – <ul>
                            <li><m>Sguir a’ chaileag a sheinn.</m>
                                <en>The girl stopped singing.</en></li>
                            <li><m>Sguiribh a dh’ithe nan ùbhlan sin!</m>
                                <en>Stop eating those apples!</en></li>
                            <li><m>Sguir an togalach a luasgadh.</m>
                                <en>The building stopped shaking.</en></li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                    <p>Some examples – <ul id="deps-comps-dhe-xs">
                            <li>human subjects – <ul>
                                    <li>pedagogical examples – <xl id="deps-comps-dhe-hum-pedag">
                                            <li>
                                                <gd>B’ fheudar dhaibh sgur de chluiche.</gd>
                                                <tr>They had to stop playing.</tr>
                                                <ref text="601">td. 524</ref>
                                            </li>
                                            <li>
                                                <gd>Sguir a dhèanamh sin!</gd>
                                                <tr>Stop doing that!</tr>
                                                <ref text="601">td. 524</ref>
                                            </li>
                                            <li>
                                                <gd>An sguir thu a throd rium?</gd>
                                                <tr>Will you stop nagging me?</tr>
                                                <ref text="601">td. 524</ref>
                                            </li>
                                            <li>
                                                <gd>Thuirt an dotair ris gum bu chòir dha sgur a
                                                  dh’obair.</gd>
                                                <tr>The doctor said to him that he ought to stop
                                                  working.</tr>
                                                <ref text="601">td. 524</ref>
                                            </li>
                                        </xl></li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>inanimate subjects – <ul>
                                    <li>pedagogical examples – <xl id="deps-comps-dhe-inanim-pedag">
                                            <li>
                                                <gd>Sguir na gunnachan a losgadh.</gd>
                                                <tr>The guns stopped firing.</tr>
                                                <ref text="601">td. 524</ref>
                                            </li>
                                        </xl></li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                    <module id="deps-comps-dhe-dheth" status="bronze">
                        <h>sguir dheth</h>
                        <p>Pedagogical examples – <xl id="deps-comps-dhe-dheth-pedag">
                                <li>
                                    <gd>Sguir dheth!</gd>
                                    <tr>Stop it!</tr>
                                    <ref text="605">td. 334</ref>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <gd>Thuirt e gum fònadh e chun a’ phoileis mura sguireadh iad
                                        dheth.</gd>
                                    <tr>He said that he would phone the police if they didn’t stop
                                        [it].</tr>
                                    <ref text="601">td. 524</ref>
                                </li>
                            </xl>
                        </p>
                    </module>
                </module>
